 :tx/rationale "EMBEDDER-CONSISTENCY PROPOSAL: The embedding vector space must be consistent across all datom-producing commands. Currently innate_concept_datoms() in concept.rs always uses HashEmbedder (line 478). If CLI observe uses model2vec Embedder, the innate concept embeddings (hash-based) live in a different vector space from observation embeddings (model-based). Cosine similarity between different vector spaces is meaningless — this would produce WORSE results than hash-only. SOLUTION: Lazy re-embedding. On first 'braid observe' with a model embedder, detect that innate concepts have hash embeddings (store a :concept/embedder-type datom). If mismatch, re-embed innate concept descriptions with the model embedder and update the concept embedding datoms. This is a one-time migration per store that runs transparently. ALTERNATIVE: Store both hash and model embeddings for each concept. Use the one matching the current embedder. REJECTED: doubles storage, adds complexity. ALTERNATIVE: Always use hash embedder for innate concepts, lower JOIN_THRESHOLD for hash-vs-hash matches. REJECTED: defeats the purpose — the whole point is semantic similarity, not keyword overlap. VERIFICATION: (A) After re-embedding, cosine(innate_anomalies_model, observation_model) produces meaningful values. (B) Re-embedding is idempotent. (C) Hash-only stores continue to work without degradation."
